  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-section">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>How long does the battery last on a wireless LED mask?</strong>
      <p>Most wireless masks get 3–5 sessions per charge (10–20 minutes each). This model lasts about 4 sessions before needing a recharge via USB-C. If you use it 4 times per week, you'll charge it weekly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Is wireless LED therapy less powerful than wired?</strong>
      <p>Not necessarily. Power depends on LED count and wavelength accuracy, not the power source. This mask uses the same clinical wavelengths as wired models. Battery constraints sometimes mean slightly lower intensity, but the difference is modest.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Can you wear this while working or cooking?</strong>
      <p>Yes—that's the main advantage. No cord means you can move freely. The mask weighs under 300g and stays secure with the adjustable strap. Use it while working at a desk, reading, cooking, or watching TV.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Do LED masks work on dark skin tones?</strong>
      <p>Yes. Red and near-infrared light penetrate all skin tones effectively. LED therapy doesn't rely on melanin absorption like some laser treatments. Clinical studies show efficacy across all skin types.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>How do you clean an LED face mask?</strong>
      <p>Wipe the silicone interior with a soft cloth and gentle cleanser after each use. Never submerge the electronics in water. Most masks have removable silicone liners that can be hand-washed separately.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

